1. Prompt 1: Design System, Core Variables, Header & Footer

Act as an expert frontend developer and UI/UX designer. Create a highly professional, modern, and fully responsive Header and Footer layout using semantic HTML5 and Vanilla CSS for a Nigerian hospital website.

Project Details:
- Hospital Name: Esther Heritage Specialist Clinic Ltd
- Colors to use via CSS :root variables:
  * --color-primary-light: #a0cbf8;
    --color-primary-dark: #537f8e;
    --color-accent: #0056b3;
  * Backgrounds/Neutrals: White, Sky Blue, and Deep Blue (for footer)
- Typography: Clear, modern sans-serif fonts suitable for healthcare.

Prompt 2: Header Requirements:
- Top Left: Font Awesome Hospital icon logo + Brand name ("Esther Heritage Specialist Clinic Ltd").
- Top Right: A prominent "Book Appointment" button with smooth hover effects.
- Center Navigation: Centered layout with standard spacing. 
  * Main Navigation Items: Home, About, Services, Departments, Customer Care & Contact.
  * Every navigation link must feature an individual, beautifully styled dropdown menu with perfect padding, drop-shadow, and a smooth fade-in slide down animation on hover. Each dropdown link should point to its respective page (index.html, about.html, services.html, etc.).

Footer Requirements:
- To be maintained identically across all pages.
- Divided into columns: 
  * Column 1: Hospital branding, short bio, and links to Social Media handles (Facebook, LinkedIn, Instagram, X via Font Awesome).
  * Column 2: Quick Links.
  * Column 3: Contact Info (Address: New Artisan, Enugu State; Phone; Email).
  * Column 4: A beautifully styled Newsletter Subscription Form (Input box + Subscribe button).

Responsiveness:
- Ensure the header transforms into a clean, functional hamburger menu on mobile and tablet devices, and the footer columns stack elegantly.
- Provide clean, commented HTML and Vanilla CSS files. Do not mix them.
Prompt 2: The Homepage (index.html)
Use this prompt to build the main entrance of your website.


2. Prompt 2: For The Hero Sections (index.html);
    1. Hero Section:
    - Background: A full-screen or high-impact hospital building background image (overlayed with a dark tint for text readability).
    - Layout: Text and elements positioned cleanly to the right side of the screen.
    - Content: A compelling headline, brief introductory text, and two call-to-action buttons side-by-side: "Book Appointment" and "Watch Video" (with a play icon wrapper).
    - Bottom Overlay Container: At the base of the hero section, overlay a 4-column feature grid containing clean Font Awesome icons and brief text for:
        * Expert Doctors
        * Advanced Care
        * 24/7 Services
        * Patient Care

    2. Section Alternation & Styling:
    - Every section following the Hero must alternate background colors precisely: Sky Blue, White, and #537f8e. Ensure the text color contrast is perfectly readable against each background.
    - Design an introduction/preview section explaining the clinic's high-tier delivery to prompt users to explore deeper.

    3. Responsiveness:
    - Make the 4-column overlay stack into 2-columns on tablets and 1-column on mobile.
    - Provide clean, separate HTML and CSS code blocks.

3. Prompt 3: The About Page (about.html)
Use this prompt to build the storytelling page honoring the legacy.

Act as an expert frontend UI/UX developer. Create a dedicated About Us page (about.html) for the hospital that carries deep emotional weight and a professional corporate look. It must utilize the same global header, footer, and CSS :root variables.

Page Content Requirements:
- Title Banner: A clean banner with a nice medical/hospital background image.
- The Story Section (Legacy & Transition): 
  * Explicitly tell the story: The clinic's founder is late, but her legacy continues through her 3 children—all qualified doctors—who have taken up the mantle to run the clinic in her demise. 
  * Because of this heritage, highlight that the hospital is transitioning/honoring her under the name: "Esther Heritage Specialist Hospital" (subsidiary/evolution of IconCare).
  * Mention that the hospital offers extensive care ranging from modern Diagnostics to deep Specialist Consultations.
- Media Layout: Place a high-quality, centered image placeholder representing the family legacy/medical leadership right in the middle of this section, surrounded by beautifully styled typography.
- Alternating Section Layouts: Maintain the alternating background scheme (Sky Blue, White, #537f8e) for additional sub-sections like "Our Mission" and "Our Vision".


4. Prompt 4: The Services Page (services.html)
Use this prompt to create a rich grid showcasing medical and wellness offerings.

Plaintext
Act as an expert frontend developer. Build a rich, highly visual Services page (services.html) for the hospital. It must utilize the same global design system and alternate colors cleanly.

Key Elements to Implement:
1. Services Grid/Flexbox Layout:
   - Use CSS Grid or Flexbox to build a modern grid of service cards. Each card must feature a distinct Font Awesome icon, a bold heading, and a description.
   - Must highlight specific capabilities: Medical Surgical Care, Fitness & Wellness Programs, advanced ECG Diagnostics, and full in-house Pharmacy Services.
   - Add hover micro-interactions to the cards (e.g., subtle lift, shadow changes, color shifts).

2. "Meet Our Specialist Doctors" Section:
   - A beautifully styled card grid featuring profile blocks for individual doctors.
   - Use descriptions tailored to professional Nigerian doctors (e.g., Consultant Cardiologist, Chief Surgeon, OB/GYN).
   - Include individual image placeholders for each doctor, professional tags, and a "View Schedule" link.

Ensure the layouts are thoroughly responsive (fluid columns shifting from 3 or 4 down to 1 on mobile screens). Give the HTML and CSS separately.
Prompt 5: The Departments Page (departments.html)
Use this prompt to elaborate on clinical divisions.

5. Prompt 5: The Department Section(department.html)
Act as an expert frontend developer. Create a clean, informative Departments page (departments.html) using HTML5 and Vanilla CSS that matches the global layout variables.

Requirements:
- Department Showcases: Design a clean layout showing how different clinical departments function together to provide premium care for patients.
- Departments to feature: Pediatrics, Obstetrics & Gynecology, General Surgery, Internal Medicine, and Emergency Care.
- For each department card or row, include:
  * A clear, descriptive icon.
  * An explanation of *how* that specific department helps care for patients safely and efficiently.
  * A call-to-action link reading "Learn Department Guidelines" or "Book Specialist".
- Layout: Alternate layouts (e.g., Image left / Text right, then Text left / Image right) using the specified background colors (Sky Blue, White, #537f8e) to keep the UI/UX engaging.

Provide the complete semantic HTML and responsive CSS.


6. Prompt 6: Customer Services & Contact Page (contact.html)
Use this prompt to build the consolidated communication page.

Act as an expert frontend developer. Build a consolidated Customer Services and Contact Us page (contact.html) to minimize excessive navigation while delivering an excellent user experience.

Requirements:
1. Customer Care Section:
   - Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) accordions styled cleanly with smooth CSS transitions when opening/closing.
   - Patient Rights and Care Support hotlines prominently displayed with large icons.

2. Contact Section:
   - Left Side / Column 1: Physical contact details beautifully arranged.
     * Address: New Artisan, Enugu State, Nigeria.
     * Click-to-call phone numbers and professional email addresses.
     * Social Media links embedded using modern medical-colored icon circles.
   - Right Side / Column 2: A sleek, modern Contact/Inquiry Form.
     * Fields: Full Name, Email, Phone Number, Selection Dropdown (Inquiry, Feedback, Complaint), and a Message Textarea.
     * Styled input fields with smooth focus states (using the primary blues), floating labels, and a striking submit button.

Ensure the layout shifts from a side-by-side 2-column view on desktop to a stacked single-column layout on mobile devices. Provide separate HTML and Vanilla CSS.
